{"title":"Bloodbane","url":"http://crawl.chaosforge.org/Bloodbane","type":"markdown","data":"***Obsolete**: This article refers to an aspect of the game which has been removed. It is retained for historical reference only.*\n\n|   |                                                                                                                                          |\n| - | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n|   | A blade forged in Hell by the sacrifice of countless tortured souls. It inflicts the rage and suffering of those souls upon its wielder. |\n\n[![Demon blade bloodbane.png](/images/c/c0/Demon_blade_bloodbane.png)](/File:Demon_blade_bloodbane.png) ***the +8 demon blade \"Bloodbane\"***\n\n+8 [demon blade](/Demon_blade \"Demon blade\")\n\n[Vorpal](/Vorpal \"Vorpal\") brand  \nAllows [berserk](/Berserk \"Berserk\")  \nForces berserk (on 5% of attacks)  \n-50 [stealth](/Stealth \"Stealth\")\n\n## Desirability\n\n**Bloodbane** is an endgame quality weapon, but going berserk on random very risky. Being [undead](/Undead \"Undead\") or having [clarity](/Clarity \"Clarity\") will prevent berserkitis, allowing you to use a +8 vorpal demon blade with minimal penalty. Since Bloodbane doesn't [curse](/Curse \"Curse\") itself on equip, other characters can switch to in situations where berserking is safe.\n\n## History\n\n- Bloodbane was removed in [0.25](/0.25 \"0.25\"). Its berserking mechanics were added to the other unrandart demon blade, [Leech](/Leech \"Leech\").\n- Prior to [0.18](/0.18 \"0.18\"), the forced berserk happened on 9% of attacks.\n- Prior to [0.15](/0.15 \"0.15\"), the stealth penalty was -20.\n- Truly a shapeshifting weapon, Bloodbane was originally a [long sword](/Long_sword \"Long sword\"), then a [katana](/Katana \"Katana\") (even after katanas were removed in [0.9](/0.9 \"0.9\")), and is now a demon blade.\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html c